WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: hr

00:00:00.669 --> 00:00:06.241
Dear young people, I’m sure you all know
this passage well – the one from Holy

00:00:06.241 --> 00:00:11.070
Scripture, from the Gospel according to
John, known as the High Priestly Prayer.

00:00:11.070 --> 00:00:17.013
Why is it that we hear precisely this
passage on the eve of the feast of

00:00:17.013 --> 00:00:21.099
Pentecost, when for these last few
Sundays Jesus has been continually

00:00:21.099 --> 00:00:25.928
taking his leave of his disciples,
and we know this text came about

00:00:25.928 --> 00:00:28.529
at the moment of the Last Supper?

00:00:29.350 --> 00:00:35.243
And why is it that, just before the
feast and solemnity of Pentecost, we

00:00:35.243 --> 00:00:37.769
hear these farewell words of Jesus?

00:00:37.769 --> 00:00:43.663
First of all, we know that among
the Jews only the priest could enter

00:00:43.663 --> 00:00:46.610
the Temple to pray for the people.

00:00:46.610 --> 00:00:50.819
Here, if you were listening
carefully, Jesus speaks and addresses

00:00:50.819 --> 00:00:53.345
the Father not only for himself.

00:00:53.345 --> 00:01:00.081
Jesus prays both for those whom God has
already given him and for those who will

00:01:00.081 --> 00:01:03.870
come after them – that is, for all of us.

00:01:03.930 --> 00:01:09.261
Jesus intercedes in advance for all
of us, and in doing so he shows this

00:01:09.261 --> 00:01:12.460
dimension of his too: that he is a priest.

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:17.792
For if, in the Jewish tradition, only a
priest could enter the Temple and plead

00:01:17.792 --> 00:01:23.834
on behalf of the people, here we see Jesus
doing precisely that for every one of us.

00:01:23.834 --> 00:01:25.612
He prays ahead of time.

00:01:25.612 --> 00:01:27.389
What does Jesus pray for?

00:01:27.389 --> 00:01:30.232
What did he pray for in this prayer?

00:01:30.232 --> 00:01:32.010
He prayed for three things.

00:01:33.170 --> 00:01:39.738
He prayed about what we struggle
with most today, and he prayed

00:01:39.738 --> 00:01:43.022
for what affects us most deeply.

00:01:43.022 --> 00:01:46.854
He prayed, first and foremost, for unity.

00:01:46.854 --> 00:01:51.233
Secondly, he prayed for our
sanctification, and thirdly

00:01:51.233 --> 00:01:53.970
he prayed again for unity.

00:01:53.970 --> 00:01:59.991
You see, Jesus begins by
praying for unity in the Church.

00:01:59.991 --> 00:02:08.749
If the Church were just a church – merely
a group of people who gather here or

00:02:08.749 --> 00:02:15.318
elsewhere in the world simply because of
certain beliefs and certain commandments

00:02:15.318 --> 00:02:19.150
– then it would not be Christ’s Church.

00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:25.360
Because we see that when Jesus
prays, when he turns to the Father,

00:02:25.360 --> 00:02:30.450
the Father gives everything to him,
and Jesus gives it back to him.

00:02:30.450 --> 00:02:34.756
And here they speak about their
communion within the Holy Trinity.

00:02:34.756 --> 00:02:40.238
The first thing we can learn tonight from
this passage is the relationship within

00:02:40.238 --> 00:02:42.587
the Holy Trinity: an unceasing giving.

00:02:42.587 --> 00:02:48.852
And the Holy Spirit is that love that
flows from the Father and the Son, the

00:02:48.852 --> 00:02:50.810
love that binds everything together.

00:02:51.590 --> 00:02:57.108
And that’s why Jesus doesn’t want
a Church that’s cold, a Church that

00:02:57.108 --> 00:03:01.778
isn’t connected, a Church that’s
just about rules and some shared

00:03:01.778 --> 00:03:04.325
standards we happen to believe in.

00:03:04.325 --> 00:03:08.570
No—Jesus wants us, if we want
to be authentic witnesses,

00:03:08.570 --> 00:03:11.117
to be like the Holy Trinity.

00:03:11.117 --> 00:03:15.362
We must be filled with
that love of God—that’s it.

00:03:15.362 --> 00:03:20.031
On the eve of Pentecost, Jesus
prays that the Holy Spirit

00:03:20.031 --> 00:03:21.730
would unite all Christians.

00:03:22.350 --> 00:03:27.618
Can we say this picture tonight, here:
that we’re all connected in spirit?

00:03:27.618 --> 00:03:32.887
Jesus isn’t asking that we instantly
love every baptised person we see that

00:03:32.887 --> 00:03:35.724
much, but that we be spiritually united.

00:03:35.724 --> 00:03:37.750
Because Jesus prays for unity.

00:03:37.750 --> 00:03:43.019
What is it that tears the Church apart,
what tears our parish communities

00:03:43.019 --> 00:03:47.883
apart, what tears our choirs apart,
what—what tears apart our prayer, erm,

00:03:47.883 --> 00:03:50.720
groups in the parishes, I don’t know.

00:03:51.710 --> 00:03:53.393
Disunity, jealousy, envy, slander.

00:03:53.393 --> 00:03:56.339
That is not the Spirit of God.

00:03:56.339 --> 00:04:01.389
Even within the Church itself
you can see how some, in their

00:04:01.389 --> 00:04:06.018
ministry, are serving that evil
spirit more than the Holy Spirit.

00:04:06.018 --> 00:04:08.964
Because the Holy Spirit is not jealous.

00:04:08.964 --> 00:04:10.647
The Holy Spirit unites.

00:04:10.647 --> 00:04:16.959
And look at the history of the Church—how
many divisions there have been, how many

00:04:16.959 --> 00:04:22.010
sins were committed precisely because we
weren’t united, we didn’t bear witness.

00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:27.942
You now have families in Croatia
who, within themselves, are no

00:04:27.942 --> 00:04:30.039
longer a little holy Church.

00:04:30.039 --> 00:04:34.232
Because you have some who
believe and some who don’t.

00:04:34.232 --> 00:04:36.328
Today you have sacramental marriages.

00:04:36.328 --> 00:04:41.780
You know that in the sacrament of
marriage, it says they become one.

00:04:41.780 --> 00:04:46.392
Yet you have those who have
just got married and have

00:04:46.392 --> 00:04:48.070
never, spiritually, become one.

00:04:48.110 --> 00:04:50.087
They became one on paper.

00:04:50.087 --> 00:04:55.229
And it is precisely Jesus’ desire – where
he intercedes and prays – first and

00:04:55.229 --> 00:05:01.162
foremost for the unity of the Church
as his Body, and that unity can be

00:05:01.162 --> 00:05:03.931
brought about only by the Holy Spirit.

00:05:03.931 --> 00:05:10.655
And so the first thing he prays for
is that we may all become one, just as

00:05:10.655 --> 00:05:15.798
the relationship between him and the
Father is, where the Holy Spirit flows

00:05:15.798 --> 00:05:20.149
and binds everything together, and
which is shown in unceasing communion.

00:05:20.830 --> 00:05:25.636
That’s why this communion matters
so much to Jesus, because he knew

00:05:25.636 --> 00:05:28.039
where the devil would strike hardest.

00:05:28.039 --> 00:05:32.444
Whenever the devil wants to destroy
something, he sows division, he

00:05:32.444 --> 00:05:37.251
brings unrest, he stirs up gossip, he
breeds jealousy—because in that way,

00:05:37.251 --> 00:05:42.858
if a person isn’t open to the grace
of the Holy Spirit, they’ll start

00:05:42.858 --> 00:05:44.860
listening to these other spirits.

00:05:44.860 --> 00:05:51.269
Secondly, Jesus says that he is going
away, and that we are not of this world.

00:05:52.069 --> 00:05:55.809
So, elsewhere, alongside that unity,
Jesus also prays for our sanctification.

00:05:55.809 --> 00:06:01.589
How does he put it: “You are in the
world, but you are not of this world”?

00:06:04.701 --> 00:06:09.556
So, because Jesus knows that, yes,
we live in this world, he prays

00:06:09.556 --> 00:06:15.158
for the gift of the Holy Spirit to
be given to us, because the Holy

00:06:15.158 --> 00:06:17.772
Spirit sets us apart from this world.

00:06:17.772 --> 00:06:22.254
If we are not open to the
Holy Spirit, then we draw

00:06:22.254 --> 00:06:24.495
from the spirit of this world.

00:06:24.495 --> 00:06:25.989
OK, Jesus is God.

00:06:25.989 --> 00:06:30.097
He lived in this world, but
he never belonged to it.

00:06:30.097 --> 00:06:35.699
Jesus himself was, all the time, waiting
for his departure, and that’s why he says:

00:06:35.699 --> 00:06:39.061
“I am going to prepare a place for you.”

00:06:40.021 --> 00:06:47.119
We are here right now, but spiritually we
can be set apart if we are God’s children,

00:06:47.119 --> 00:06:50.460
if we are filled with the Holy Spirit.

00:06:50.460 --> 00:06:57.558
And that’s why Jesus says we are in this
world, but we are not of this world.

00:06:57.558 --> 00:07:03.404
In other words, he means we don’t
identify with the spirit of this world.

00:07:03.404 --> 00:07:05.075
That’s the problem today.

00:07:05.075 --> 00:07:10.921
So, many people open themselves up to
all sorts of spirits of this world.

00:07:11.721 --> 00:07:16.607
Many people are filled with, I don’t
know, all sorts of different spirits.

00:07:16.607 --> 00:07:21.118
I always say: everyone is spiritual;
it’s just a question of which

00:07:21.118 --> 00:07:22.621
spirit they’re filled with.

00:07:22.621 --> 00:07:25.629
Even those who say they’re
Christians and believers.

00:07:25.629 --> 00:07:31.267
But I always say the measure of that
is the fruit of the Holy Spirit.

00:07:31.267 --> 00:07:36.906
That’s why Jesus says, “You are in
this world, but you are not of it.”

00:07:38.026 --> 00:07:42.862
Because God Himself, as God,
was set apart from this world.

00:07:42.862 --> 00:07:45.940
Jesus knew what His
destination was: heaven.

00:07:45.940 --> 00:07:50.337
And that’s why, elsewhere, He prays
for our personal sanctification;

00:07:50.337 --> 00:07:54.734
and our personal sanctification
comes through the grace, the zeal,

00:07:54.734 --> 00:07:57.812
and the fire of the Holy Spirit.

00:07:57.812 --> 00:08:04.408
For when a person is filled with the
Holy Spirit, they know exactly when the

00:08:04.408 --> 00:08:07.486
spirit of this world is attacking them.

00:08:08.206 --> 00:08:14.663
I always say that the Holy Spirit
within us is a kind of alarm.

00:08:14.663 --> 00:08:19.736
Whenever something worldly is false,
because the father of lies often

00:08:19.736 --> 00:08:24.810
deceives in his own way, even through
disguised projects, ideas, erm,

00:08:24.810 --> 00:08:27.116
visions, he finds his followers.

00:08:27.116 --> 00:08:32.651
And then a person can throw themselves
into something, thinking they’re fighting

00:08:32.651 --> 00:08:38.186
for it, without even realising they’re
actually fighting on the wrong side.

00:08:39.086 --> 00:08:44.293
How often today do we see these various
initiatives, people who are, in inverted

00:08:44.293 --> 00:08:49.128
commas, fighting for human rights,
for the dignity of this or that, and

00:08:49.128 --> 00:08:53.591
yet in reality they’re serving the
spirit of this world, serving the

00:08:53.591 --> 00:08:56.195
spirit of death, the spirit of murder.

00:08:56.195 --> 00:09:01.030
I don’t, I don’t, I don’t understand
it, but sin so often blinds.

00:09:01.030 --> 00:09:05.866
And that’s why Jesus says: “No,
no. You cannot be conformed to it.”

00:09:05.906 --> 00:09:07.936
That isn’t the spirit of sanctification.

00:09:07.936 --> 00:09:13.351
The spirit of sanctification is the one
who listens to my word, the one who allows

00:09:13.351 --> 00:09:17.412
himself to be sanctified in humility.”
And that’s why, elsewhere, alongside that

00:09:17.412 --> 00:09:22.149
communion, Jesus calls us to be sanctified
by the power of the Holy Spirit.

00:09:22.149 --> 00:09:27.226
Because you can be in this world and
yet be filled with the Holy Spirit.

00:09:29.754 --> 00:09:33.246
And I said that in one of my sermons.

00:09:33.246 --> 00:09:38.292
Yesterday someone asked me on a podcast
how—how, when you’re in the faith—how

00:09:38.292 --> 00:09:44.114
to get rid of bad people around you,
how to recognise the evil around you.

00:09:44.193 --> 00:09:46.125
You don’t need to do anything.

00:09:46.125 --> 00:09:47.413
Just belong to God.

00:09:47.413 --> 00:09:49.345
Everything around you will fall away.

00:09:49.345 --> 00:09:51.599
All the devils will leave you alone.

00:09:51.599 --> 00:09:53.853
Just be filled with the Holy Spirit.

00:09:53.853 --> 00:09:55.785
You’ll be a nuisance to everyone.

00:09:55.785 --> 00:09:59.650
How will you know whether
you’re of this world or of God?

00:09:59.650 --> 00:10:03.836
Like this: if you’re God’s, you’ll
even get on your own mum’s and

00:10:03.836 --> 00:10:07.700
dad’s nerves—so of course you’ll
get on the devil’s nerves too, and

00:10:07.700 --> 00:10:09.633
everyone else who works against God.

00:10:11.073 --> 00:10:13.136
I believe, young people, that you
yourselves have experienced your

00:10:13.136 --> 00:10:15.406
own parents saying to you: “Don’t
go overboard with your faith.

00:10:15.406 --> 00:10:18.708
Why are you going up there every Thursday
and on Sundays, why are you always going

00:10:18.708 --> 00:10:20.153
to church—what’s going to become of you?”

00:10:23.501 --> 00:10:27.556
Anyone who lives by the spirit
of this world cannot understand

00:10:27.556 --> 00:10:29.030
what spiritual hunger is.

00:10:29.030 --> 00:10:30.874
Thank God you are hungry.

00:10:30.874 --> 00:10:36.403
Thank God there is the Holy Spirit who
awakens in people the desire to come

00:10:36.403 --> 00:10:41.933
to the source, to drink deeply and
to seek the fire of the Holy Spirit.

00:10:41.933 --> 00:10:46.726
And I’m actually afraid of those
who say they wouldn’t want to overdo

00:10:46.726 --> 00:10:51.150
it, who’ve reduced their devotion
to the bare minimum and that’s that.

00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:56.375
Well, you’re of this world, because you
won’t let yourself be pulled away from

00:10:56.375 --> 00:10:57.756
what’s attractive, from this world.

00:10:57.756 --> 00:11:02.174
If spirituality is too much for you, then
ask yourself why too much money isn’t too

00:11:02.174 --> 00:11:04.383
much, why too much career isn’t too much.

00:11:04.383 --> 00:11:07.145
That’s why you’re hungry, you
gorge yourself, you work yourself

00:11:07.145 --> 00:11:08.802
to death twenty-four hours a day.

00:11:08.802 --> 00:11:13.220
That’s not a problem for you, but
if you go to Mass twice on a Sunday,

00:11:13.220 --> 00:11:16.810
or to some prayer meeting, there you
go—people say you’ve gone completely mad.

00:11:18.310 --> 00:11:21.766
Better to be mad about
Jesus than about Satan.

00:11:21.766 --> 00:11:26.376
Today, many are mad about the devil,
running after him, and they’re

00:11:26.376 --> 00:11:30.985
not even aware of it because they
don’t see who they’re chasing.

00:11:30.985 --> 00:11:34.442
For behind the devil there’s
always something hidden — something

00:11:34.442 --> 00:11:36.363
he’s used to hook them.

00:11:36.363 --> 00:11:40.588
And now you can imagine: he just
keeps shifting those boundaries.

00:11:40.588 --> 00:11:43.661
Where does this hunger for the world end?

00:11:43.661 --> 00:11:46.349
Wars are fought, and the innocent suffer.

00:11:46.729 --> 00:11:47.134
Why?

00:11:47.134 --> 00:11:52.399
Because of the curse, because of hunger,
because of greed, because of power.

00:11:52.399 --> 00:11:55.233
That is the spirit of this world.

00:11:55.233 --> 00:11:56.853
That is Satan’s instrument.

00:11:56.853 --> 00:11:59.687
So, dear young people, don’t be afraid.

00:11:59.687 --> 00:12:04.546
Don’t be afraid when they call
you out, when they mock you.

00:12:04.546 --> 00:12:09.811
“Have peace in your heart, for
I am not of this world,” say.

00:12:09.811 --> 00:12:14.265
I am in it, but I long for
higher, heavenly gifts.

00:12:14.265 --> 00:12:16.290
I long for eternal life.

00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:19.046
I long for peace in my heart.

00:12:19.046 --> 00:12:21.100
I long for a clear conscience.

00:12:21.100 --> 00:12:23.838
To be able to lie down in bed.

00:12:23.838 --> 00:12:28.631
I long to be able to look every
brother and sister in the eye

00:12:28.631 --> 00:12:30.685
with love, to hate no one.

00:12:30.685 --> 00:12:33.766
I want my spiritual life to be in order.

00:12:33.766 --> 00:12:39.243
When they offer you all this wealth of
the world, every kind of power, money and

00:12:39.243 --> 00:12:41.639
everything else, people, be on your guard.

00:12:41.639 --> 00:12:43.009
Be on your guard.

00:12:43.009 --> 00:12:44.378
You will lose yourself.

00:12:44.378 --> 00:12:46.089
Many people have lost themselves.

00:12:46.550 --> 00:12:51.770
They’ve got everything I listed
before, but they haven’t got peace.

00:12:51.770 --> 00:12:54.618
They’ve no time to sleep soundly.

00:12:54.618 --> 00:13:00.314
Because, look, sometimes it seems
people use us, and sometimes we think

00:13:00.314 --> 00:13:03.161
we’re naïve just because we’re good.

00:13:03.161 --> 00:13:08.857
But don’t worry: both those
who sow good and those who sow

00:13:08.857 --> 00:13:13.603
evil—everything will be repaid;
everyone will reap what they’ve sown.

00:13:13.603 --> 00:13:18.349
It’s only a question of when
each person will harvest.

00:13:19.250 --> 00:13:20.595
So don’t be disappointed.

00:13:20.595 --> 00:13:24.966
Sometimes I see Christians who are
disappointed and say, “Oh, it’s just not

00:13:24.966 --> 00:13:28.665
worth being good, because look—everyone
tramples all over me.” They don’t.

00:13:28.665 --> 00:13:32.365
When the time comes, Jesus
will stand up in your defence.

00:13:32.365 --> 00:13:37.745
And I ask myself: for the one who
serves Satan, who will stand up for him?

00:13:37.745 --> 00:13:38.081
Who?

00:13:38.081 --> 00:13:43.126
So don’t be afraid to open yourselves
to the Holy Spirit and say, “I belong

00:13:43.126 --> 00:13:47.834
to God.” Yes, you’re in this world,
and when they criticise you as modern

00:13:47.834 --> 00:13:51.197
Catholics—young people—“Are you normal,
living pre-marital chastity?” We can see

00:13:51.197 --> 00:13:55.905
it’s become something people now mock,
they sneer at it, as if you’re stupid.

00:13:57.366 --> 00:14:02.074
Tell them, “I’m not stupid, because
I’m not just flesh and body.

00:14:02.074 --> 00:14:07.566
I have a heart, I have a conscience,
I have morals, I have values.

00:14:07.566 --> 00:14:13.059
I’m doing this for my own good.” Don’t
fall into temptation, because you see,

00:14:13.059 --> 00:14:18.552
that’s exactly what Satan does too: he
often tries to convince us, through other

00:14:18.552 --> 00:14:21.298
people, that we’re on the wrong path.

00:14:21.298 --> 00:14:21.690
No.

00:14:21.690 --> 00:14:23.260
Look, Jesus knew this.

00:14:23.260 --> 00:14:27.575
That’s why Jesus prays for our
sanctification, because if we want

00:14:27.575 --> 00:14:33.460
to live out this word of God, we
have to go against the current – and

00:14:33.460 --> 00:14:35.030
that’s unavoidable for everyone.

00:14:36.930 --> 00:14:39.726
And that’s why Jesus intercedes for us.

00:14:39.726 --> 00:14:46.116
Just remember this: Jesus knew all of this
in advance, and that’s why he prayed for

00:14:46.116 --> 00:14:48.513
all of us—for unity, for sanctification.

00:14:48.513 --> 00:14:50.910
Thirdly, what did Jesus pray for?

00:14:50.910 --> 00:14:55.303
He prayed for truth, that we
might remain in the truth.

00:14:55.303 --> 00:15:02.093
He will send the Holy Spirit, he says, to
lead us into all truth—and not everyone in

00:15:02.093 --> 00:15:04.890
the world can recognise the Holy Spirit.

00:15:06.069 --> 00:15:06.903
I can’t.

00:15:06.903 --> 00:15:13.986
At the start of Mass I said: the worst
kind of people are those who have their

00:15:13.986 --> 00:15:16.486
eyes open, but their hearts closed.

00:15:16.486 --> 00:15:18.569
Nothing gets through to them.

00:15:18.569 --> 00:15:23.569
So, in this world we constantly
keep our eyes on the lookout.

00:15:23.569 --> 00:15:27.736
We’re always guarding against enemies,
watching out for—say—competition at work.

00:15:27.736 --> 00:15:32.736
You watch this, you watch that,
so you don’t make a mistake.

00:15:32.736 --> 00:15:38.569
We’ve got our eyes wide open like
this, staring—but it does you no good.

00:15:39.270 --> 00:15:44.319
That’s useful for the rat race
in this world, but you need to

00:15:44.319 --> 00:15:46.262
have your spiritual eyes open.

00:15:46.262 --> 00:15:50.923
Have you ever wondered why, for
forty days, Jesus kept appearing to

00:15:50.923 --> 00:15:55.584
the disciples—he’d show up and then
disappear, show up and then disappear.

00:15:55.584 --> 00:15:55.973
Why?

00:15:55.973 --> 00:16:00.246
He wasn’t playing hide-and-seek
with them; he wanted to get them

00:16:00.246 --> 00:16:04.907
used to stopping looking for him
like this with their physical eyes,

00:16:04.907 --> 00:16:06.849
and instead with spiritual eyes.

00:16:07.709 --> 00:16:13.473
He wanted to get them used to recognising
him with the heart, in a spiritual way,

00:16:13.473 --> 00:16:18.876
and that’s what Jesus tells us: “I will
send the Advocate, who will remain with

00:16:18.876 --> 00:16:23.919
you — the Spirit of truth — always.”
And only those with an open heart, with

00:16:23.919 --> 00:16:28.602
spiritual eyes opened, will be able to
recognise him — not these bulging eyes,

00:16:28.602 --> 00:16:33.285
these greedy eyes, these eyes that are
never satisfied, that only want more,

00:16:33.285 --> 00:16:38.688
that trample on human dignity at the
cost of excuses and lies just to please

00:16:38.688 --> 00:16:40.490
themselves and soothe their conscience.

00:16:42.769 --> 00:16:48.385
So, dear young people, Jesus calls us;
he tells us to remain in the truth,

00:16:48.385 --> 00:16:51.380
and the truth is his word, his word.

00:16:51.380 --> 00:16:58.119
And now, as we go on to look at it, Jesus
prayed for all three of those things.

00:16:58.119 --> 00:16:59.617
Have they been fulfilled?

00:16:59.617 --> 00:16:59.991
Yes.

00:16:59.991 --> 00:17:04.858
But we’ll ask the question: have
they been fulfilled in our own lives?

00:17:04.858 --> 00:17:05.981
Well, that’s different.

00:17:05.981 --> 00:17:10.848
If we look at how Jesus prayed
for the unity of the Church.

00:17:13.137 --> 00:17:16.994
Those fruits were seen straight
away when Jesus ascended into

00:17:16.994 --> 00:17:21.237
heaven: the first apostles received
the gift of the Holy Spirit.

00:17:21.237 --> 00:17:25.095
They opened themselves up and
went out into the streets.

00:17:25.095 --> 00:17:30.110
They loved their fellow Christians so
much that they were ready to preach

00:17:30.110 --> 00:17:32.810
at the cost of their own lives.

00:17:32.810 --> 00:17:37.053
They were so committed to those small
churches they were founding—caring

00:17:37.053 --> 00:17:38.982
for them, writing them letters.

00:17:38.982 --> 00:17:42.454
Saint Paul and Saint Peter
would travel around, encouraging

00:17:42.454 --> 00:17:43.997
them and strengthening them.

00:17:45.157 --> 00:17:51.283
So you can see the fruit of
what Jesus prayed for in the

00:17:51.283 --> 00:17:53.168
early Church: unity, communion.

00:17:53.168 --> 00:17:57.880
They put everything together on
the table, shared everything, and

00:17:57.880 --> 00:18:00.236
those fruits were already visible.

00:18:00.236 --> 00:18:04.477
I ask myself: is that
visible among us today?

00:18:04.477 --> 00:18:09.661
Another fruit Jesus prayed for
was that they would become holy.

00:18:09.661 --> 00:18:16.258
Many in the early Church received gifts
of the Holy Spirit, and those gifts—along

00:18:16.258 --> 00:18:22.385
with the grace and guidance of the Holy
Spirit—protected them from this world.

00:18:23.925 --> 00:18:28.786
And you can see that Jesus succeeded
in praying for what he prayed for:

00:18:28.786 --> 00:18:32.954
that they would remain in communion
and that they would remain sanctified.

00:18:32.954 --> 00:18:37.468
And he says he also prayed that
they would remain in the truth.

00:18:37.468 --> 00:18:41.288
Were the first apostles inspired
by the Holy Spirit and did

00:18:41.288 --> 00:18:42.677
they write Holy Scripture?

00:18:42.677 --> 00:18:44.066
That is the truth.

00:18:44.066 --> 00:18:49.623
If the apostles and the first disciples
had not been open to the Holy Spirit, if

00:18:49.623 --> 00:18:54.485
they had not written down God’s truth,
we today would not have the truth.

00:18:55.466 --> 00:18:59.299
And that’s why it’s such a mercy
that this too was fulfilled.

00:18:59.299 --> 00:19:02.814
And the third intention Jesus
prayed for was that my disciples

00:19:02.814 --> 00:19:04.411
would remain in the truth.

00:19:04.411 --> 00:19:07.925
That’s why the first disciples wrote
down his commandments, his words,

00:19:07.925 --> 00:19:13.037
and passed them on to us today so
that we can live in the truth, so

00:19:13.037 --> 00:19:15.593
that we can hold fast to God’s word.

00:19:15.593 --> 00:19:19.427
And that’s why I always say: you
can’t bargain with God’s word

00:19:19.427 --> 00:19:20.705
and with God’s commandments.

00:19:21.065 --> 00:19:26.336
“I’ll keep this one, I’ll throw that
one out because I don’t like it.

00:19:26.336 --> 00:19:30.855
I think this one ought to be
kept only halfway, this one

00:19:30.855 --> 00:19:32.738
like this…” It doesn’t work.

00:19:32.738 --> 00:19:33.867
Truth is truth.

00:19:33.867 --> 00:19:38.386
Either you serve God’s word, the
truth, or you serve someone else.

00:19:38.386 --> 00:19:42.905
That’s why all three of these prayers
Jesus prayed have been fulfilled.

00:19:46.429 --> 00:19:52.161
And that’s why we’ve now got the answer
as to why, on the eve of the feast

00:19:52.161 --> 00:19:56.206
of the coming of the Holy Spirit,
Jesus prays this priestly – this

00:19:56.206 --> 00:20:00.251
high-priestly – prayer, where he
intercedes for his Church, for all of us.

00:20:00.251 --> 00:20:03.960
See how powerful that is:
Jesus prayed for us in advance.

00:20:03.960 --> 00:20:07.331
How often do we think
it all depends on us.

00:20:07.331 --> 00:20:09.017
Come on, people, wake up.

00:20:09.017 --> 00:20:13.062
Realise that our lives – everything
we are, everything we do – are in

00:20:13.062 --> 00:20:17.445
God’s hands; that God, that Jesus, has
already been thinking of us, praying

00:20:17.445 --> 00:20:22.164
in advance that trials and temptations
would pass us by, that we would remain

00:20:22.164 --> 00:20:26.884
in communion, that we would remain
in the truth, that we would be made

00:20:26.884 --> 00:20:30.929
holy – and not that we go and ascribe
certain realities to ourselves.

00:20:30.969 --> 00:20:35.530
OK, we co-operate with God,
but staying on the right path

00:20:35.530 --> 00:20:37.603
is God’s grace, God’s desire.

00:20:37.603 --> 00:20:42.164
And as I said, let’s open
ourselves to the Holy Spirit.

00:20:42.164 --> 00:20:48.798
None of this would have come about in the
early Church if the first disciples hadn’t

00:20:48.798 --> 00:20:54.602
opened themselves to the Holy Spirit; and
what he prayed for was then fulfilled—what

00:20:54.602 --> 00:20:57.090
Jesus prayed for came to pass.

00:20:57.090 --> 00:21:02.480
Jesus is surely still praying that
we too, the Church of this century,

00:21:02.480 --> 00:21:07.870
remain in those very same things: in
communion, sanctified, and in the truth.

00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:14.315
I said how much of a cancer
that is in the Church.

00:21:14.315 --> 00:21:17.875
How many poisonous tongues,
how much jealousy, how many

00:21:17.875 --> 00:21:19.457
people stir up division.

00:21:19.457 --> 00:21:21.830
Some people are walking
division—walking it.

00:21:21.830 --> 00:21:26.971
Some people are walking unrest, and yet
they’re always hanging around the church.

00:21:26.971 --> 00:21:33.695
Even here on Thursdays, how many times I’d
like to shake some of them off like slime.

00:21:33.695 --> 00:21:34.881
Because they’re unrest—unrest.

00:21:34.881 --> 00:21:37.649
Man, stop and stand before Jesus Christ.

00:21:37.810 --> 00:21:41.383
Ask yourself what you’re preaching,
what you’re testifying to.

00:21:41.383 --> 00:21:47.339
Don’t drag the name of Jesus Christ
and the faith in Jesus through the mud.

00:21:47.339 --> 00:21:52.500
Many people use the word “Jesus”, and
“faith”, to cover up their foolishness,

00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:55.279
to cover up their sins and disobedience.

00:21:55.279 --> 00:22:00.441
With people like that, the best
way to check is by their obedience.

00:22:00.441 --> 00:22:02.426
Just challenge them, warn them.

00:22:02.426 --> 00:22:06.000
Try telling them, and
you’ll see how they hiss.

00:22:06.750 --> 00:22:11.680
Then you’ll see that pious, counterfeit
spirit in them start to flare up.

00:22:11.680 --> 00:22:16.989
And they often turn themselves into some
kind of “prophets of God”, handing out

00:22:16.989 --> 00:22:22.299
their messages, advice, and I don’t know
what else. To other wounded members of

00:22:22.299 --> 00:22:27.608
the Church who are still seeking peace
in Jesus Christ, they end up confusing

00:22:27.608 --> 00:22:32.538
many believers who have decided to
return to Jesus Christ hurt and broken,

00:22:32.538 --> 00:22:37.469
and with their false “truth” they
confuse them and steer them off course.

00:22:39.289 --> 00:22:43.726
No-one else needs to guide you,
dear young people, except Jesus

00:22:43.726 --> 00:22:46.147
Christ and the Word of God.

00:22:46.147 --> 00:22:50.584
That is the truth in which
Jesus wants you to remain.

00:22:50.584 --> 00:22:55.022
Don’t listen to other voices:
there are many false prophets, many

00:22:55.022 --> 00:23:00.669
impostors who swear by God’s name, who
present themselves and put on an act.

00:23:00.669 --> 00:23:05.914
The fruits of the Holy Spirit
can be seen in all of us.

00:23:05.914 --> 00:23:12.369
Holiness isn’t shown on our faces, in the
sense that even false piety can be learnt.

00:23:13.389 --> 00:23:16.459
And many today turn those little
voices into something as if

00:23:16.459 --> 00:23:17.575
they’re working at reception.

00:23:17.575 --> 00:23:19.809
And then when that starts up, it’s just…

00:23:20.289 --> 00:23:22.315
Dear God, thank God for that.

00:23:22.315 --> 00:23:23.666
Oh, Jesus, thank you.

00:23:23.666 --> 00:23:26.369
You should, you should do it for Jesus.”

00:23:26.389 --> 00:23:30.861
When I hear that kind of imitation
holiness, honestly, I just lose it.

00:23:30.861 --> 00:23:32.925
Maybe there’s something wrong with me.

00:23:32.925 --> 00:23:36.021
Then, really, there must
be something wrong with me.

00:23:36.021 --> 00:23:41.526
I’ve been a priest for ten years and I
still haven’t got that tone of voice.

00:23:42.806 --> 00:23:44.032
Is it me?

00:23:44.032 --> 00:23:46.077
I don’t know what’s wrong.

00:23:46.077 --> 00:23:47.303
But honestly, people?

00:23:47.303 --> 00:23:52.210
Because I’m telling you, it’s not some
display of holiness and relationship

00:23:52.210 --> 00:23:55.481
with God — all of that can be learnt.

00:23:55.481 --> 00:23:59.979
Relationship is what I said:
you recognise it by its fruits.

00:23:59.979 --> 00:24:03.250
Forget the imitation, forget
it — let’s be original.

00:24:03.250 --> 00:24:08.157
Like that young lad Acutis says,
Blessed Carlo Acutis: we’re all born

00:24:08.157 --> 00:24:10.610
originals, and we die as copies.

00:24:10.610 --> 00:24:12.246
So let’s be original.

00:24:13.106 --> 00:24:18.223
So, if we are—if we belong to
Jesus—we are in this world.

00:24:18.223 --> 00:24:24.194
Let’s fight for the unity of the
Church; let’s always stand up for unity.

00:24:24.194 --> 00:24:29.739
People, don’t give the devil any
room to sow division in the Church.

00:24:29.739 --> 00:24:33.151
That most often happens on social
media—anywhere, really—whenever

00:24:33.151 --> 00:24:34.857
some story gets started.

00:24:34.857 --> 00:24:39.975
I said this once from here: what
normal believer, what normal believer

00:24:39.975 --> 00:24:45.946
would go on social media and ask,
“What do you think of this priest?”

00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:49.720
And by doing that you’ve set off an
avalanche of gossip and backbiting.

00:24:49.720 --> 00:24:52.592
Sure, someone might even say
something positive about that priest.

00:24:52.592 --> 00:24:55.752
But with that question you’ve opened
up a discussion — arguing about

00:24:55.752 --> 00:24:57.189
someone who isn’t even present.

00:24:57.189 --> 00:25:01.210
“What do you think of those prayer
groups?” “What do you think of this

00:25:01.210 --> 00:25:05.232
bishop?” “What do you think of that
one?” And then some old woman pipes

00:25:05.232 --> 00:25:06.956
up: “You lot are like devils.”

00:25:06.966 --> 00:25:10.597
So, the moment you ask a
question like that, you’re laying

00:25:10.597 --> 00:25:11.918
the groundwork for division.

00:25:11.918 --> 00:25:15.549
Because one person says this,
another says that, and then they

00:25:15.549 --> 00:25:18.521
start bickering amongst themselves
— some defending, some acting as

00:25:18.521 --> 00:25:20.171
apologists, some this, some that.

00:25:20.171 --> 00:25:21.822
You understand what I mean.

00:25:21.822 --> 00:25:27.104
These are the little things where we can
all just cut it off straight away, so

00:25:27.104 --> 00:25:29.746
that no division is created in the Church.

00:25:30.706 --> 00:25:32.066
That’s just one example.

00:25:32.066 --> 00:25:32.747
One example.

00:25:32.747 --> 00:25:37.850
And there are so many ways we can
help make sure that what Jesus prayed

00:25:37.850 --> 00:25:42.273
for — that we remain one — actually
happens: that we stay united with the

00:25:42.273 --> 00:25:46.696
Holy Spirit and pray for the grace
and strength of the Holy Spirit.

00:25:50.069 --> 00:25:54.291
The first Christians were so
closely united; they loved their

00:25:54.291 --> 00:25:55.980
Christian brothers so much.

00:25:55.980 --> 00:26:00.625
How do we talk about others – our
fellow Christian brothers – especially

00:26:00.625 --> 00:26:02.736
those who aren’t Catholic yet?

00:26:02.736 --> 00:26:05.692
What feelings do we have towards them?

00:26:05.692 --> 00:26:09.492
Oof… we could do with a
prayer for forgiveness.

00:26:09.492 --> 00:26:16.249
So, let this be an encouragement for us to
think about what really mattered to Jesus.

00:26:16.710 --> 00:26:20.323
Jesus cared about unity,
that we pray for holiness.

00:26:20.323 --> 00:26:26.346
So pray—and if you do notice something
that isn’t right, pray to the Holy Spirit

00:26:26.346 --> 00:26:28.354
for communion, pray for sanctification.

00:26:28.354 --> 00:26:31.566
In other words, let’s
not belittle one another.

00:26:31.566 --> 00:26:37.589
The other day, after I’d been a
priest for ten years, I had a man

00:26:37.589 --> 00:26:42.809
say to me, “You might turn out to
be something.” “Thanks,” I said.

00:26:45.905 --> 00:26:50.475
It’s just that, you know, I’m not the
sort who needs to prove myself to people.

00:26:50.475 --> 00:26:52.760
I know what I’m worth in God’s eyes.

00:26:52.760 --> 00:26:54.759
And it’s the same for every person.

00:26:54.759 --> 00:26:58.758
And when I say that to you,
you say it to me as well.

00:26:58.758 --> 00:27:01.900
Because if someone isn’t rooted in
God, they’ll start doubting themselves.

00:27:01.900 --> 00:27:04.471
Let’s praise one another
for what we do well.

00:27:04.471 --> 00:27:06.185
Look—your T-shirt is lovely this year.

00:27:06.226 --> 00:27:09.065
Someone just now commented
that it’s an ugly colour.

00:27:09.065 --> 00:27:13.167
No—say it, and if you can’t
swallow it, at least try to force

00:27:13.167 --> 00:27:14.744
something past those selfish lips.

00:27:14.744 --> 00:27:17.899
Praise someone for something
they do well in the church.

00:27:17.899 --> 00:27:21.370
You sing well, you serve well,
you clean these tiles well.

00:27:21.370 --> 00:27:25.156
Do you know that every Saturday the
women here clean th-this church,

00:27:25.156 --> 00:27:27.365
all of this that we mess up.

00:27:27.666 --> 00:27:29.053
Well, you should notice it.

00:27:29.053 --> 00:27:32.383
Yes, that’s the Spirit of God
then – when we notice in someone

00:27:32.383 --> 00:27:35.713
else what they’re doing well for
the Body of Christ, the Church.

00:27:35.713 --> 00:27:40.152
Look, it’s the St Anthony’s walk at the
moment, and when I see how many people

00:27:40.152 --> 00:27:43.760
are working wholeheartedly to make it
succeed, to see it through… But there

00:27:43.760 --> 00:27:45.980
are also those who work to sow division.

00:27:45.980 --> 00:27:47.922
There are also those who are jealous.

00:27:47.922 --> 00:27:49.865
There are also those who copy us.

00:27:50.185 --> 00:27:51.369
It doesn’t matter.

00:27:51.369 --> 00:27:55.711
Let’s just pray for unity, so
that Jesus may be glorified,

00:27:55.711 --> 00:27:58.079
because he cares about his body.

00:27:58.079 --> 00:27:59.658
Jesus doesn’t need buildings.

00:27:59.658 --> 00:28:04.790
What Jesus needs is us – unity
among us and peace in our hearts.

00:28:04.790 --> 00:28:05.185
Amen.

